passages.text: JEF's Weekly Flows-Soft Inflows to Small,Flow to Fin's Could be Heart Beat"

The dog days of summer played a role in flows on week with very little coming into equities. We do like the fact that Small took in close to $2B with much of that to the IWM, while we think Fin's may have seen a "Heart Beat" trade. The QQQ had another withdrawal, while GLD saw chunky inflow. Interest in Health Care has really picked up, while flows to Tech have stayed weak. Aggregate Fixed and Inv Grade each saw over $1B come in, but HY saw another withdrawal.
A nice inflow to Small Caps, more outflows from the QQQ

What's Hot: Flows heated up for Small Caps with close to \(\) 2B\$ coming into the combined funds but much of the intake taking place in the IWM. We think Finl's saw a "Heart Beat" trade and could see an outflow next week, but things have really picked up for Health Care after a very long drought. On the Credit front, Inv Grade and Aggregate Fixed each saw over \(\) 1B\$ in inflow, while over \(\) 2B\$ came into the GLD.

What's Not: More outflows from the QQQ, this time over \(\) 2B\$ , while Large Core saw a tiny outflow, but an outflow nevertheless. With the market hitting new highs, Staples is out of vogue along with Low Vol ETFs. High Yield saw another withdrawal, this one was small, however.
